# Development & Build Process

## Development Server

- Run with: `pnpm dev`
- Runs on `http://localhost:8100`
- Hot reload enabled via Vite

## Build Process

- Build command: `pnpm build`
- TypeScript compilation + Vite build
- Outputs to `dist/` directory
- Gzip compression enabled

## Package Manager

- Use `pnpm` (not npm or yarn)
- Dependencies defined in [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- Lockfile: [pnpm-lock.yaml](mdc:pnpm-lock.yaml)

## TypeScript Configuration

- Main config: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- Build config: [tsconfig.node.json](mdc:tsconfig.node.json)
- Path alias: `@` points to `src/`

## Asset Handling

- Static assets in [public/](mdc:public/) directory
- Images, fonts, and external libraries
- Imported assets go in [src/assets/](mdc:src/assets/)

## Environment Configuration

- Vite handles environment variables
- Use `VITE_` prefix for client-side variables
- Configuration in [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts)

## Code Quality

- TypeScript for type safety
- SCSS for styling
- ESLint and Prettier (if configured)
- Follow established patterns in codebase

## Performance Optimization

- Bundle splitting with Vite
- Lazy loading for routes
- Image optimization
- Gzip compression in production

## Debugging

- Use browser DevTools
- React DevTools for component inspection
- Redux DevTools for state management
- Source maps enabled in development
